13 E. If a transfer request is denied by the school district, the
14 parent of the student may appeal the denial within ten (10) days of
15 notification of the denial to the receiving school district board of
16 education. The receiving school district board of education shall
17 consider the appeal at its next regularly scheduled board meeting.
18 If the receiving school district board of education denies the
19 appeal, the parent of the student may appeal the denial within ten
20 (10) days of notification of the appeal denial to the State Board of
21 Education. The parent shall submit to the State Board of Education
22 and the superintendent of the receiving school a notice of appeal on
